/**
 * @mainpage Secure Image Download System
 *
 * @section intro Introduction
 * This project implements a secure client-server system for transferring image files
 * over a network using structured packet communication and authentication.
 *
 * @section architecture System Architecture
 * The system follows a client-server architecture:
 * - The client provides a user interface for login and image requests
 * - The server listens for connections and processes requests
 * - Communication is performed over TCP using structured packets
 *
 * @section components Components
 * The system is composed of:
 * - NetworkManager (client communication)
 * - ServerManager (server lifecycle)
 * - PacketHandler (packet serialization/deserialization)
 * - ImageTransferManager (chunked image sending)
 * - ImageManager (image reconstruction)
 * - AuthManager (authentication)
 * - StateManager (state machine control)
 *
 * @section state_machine State Machine
 * The server enforces valid behavior using a state machine:
 * - WaitingForConnection
 * - Connected
 * - Authenticated
 * - Ready
 * - SendingImage
 *
 * Transitions are strictly controlled to prevent invalid operations.
 *
 * @section packet_design Packet Design
 * Communication is handled using structured packets containing:
 * - Packet type
 * - Command ID
 * - Payload length
 * - Payload data
 * - Sequence number
 * - Validation field
 *
 * @section data_flow Data Flow
 * 1. Client sends login packet
 * 2. Server validates credentials
 * 3. Client requests image
 * 4. Server splits image into chunks
 * 5. Server sends chunks with sequence numbers
 * 6. Client reconstructs image
 *
 * @section testing Testing
 * The system includes a regression test suite using MSTest
 * to validate packet handling, authentication, and image transfer.
 *
 * @section conclusion Conclusion
 * This system demonstrates secure communication, reliable data transfer,
 * and proper architectural design principles.
 */